# Blocker / review / failure protocol

Authoritative standard: `.ai/MASTER_WORKFLOW.md` (§9, §11, §12). Safety and honesty take
precedence over speed and task completion. Never represent unfinished or failed work as success.

## REVIEW_REQUIRED — human decision or protected action
Set when a human approval, permission, credential/secret entry, external-service action,
destructive confirmation, or a commit/push/deploy/release (not already authorized) is needed.
1. Stop safely before the protected action.
2. Set `HANDOFF.md` to `REVIEW_REQUIRED`; document the exact human action required.
3. Record what was completed, what remains unchanged, whether code/config changed, and any
   uncommitted work. 4. Sync and verify immediately. 5. Do not continue until confirmed.

## BLOCKED — recoverable technical/environmental issue
1. Run only safe, scoped diagnostics; make no speculative destructive changes.
2. If unresolved, set `BLOCKED`; record the failed command, concise error evidence, and the last
   successful step. 3. Sync and verify immediately. 4. Wait for guidance.

## FAILED — task or critical validation failed
1. Stop further changes; preserve evidence and current work. 2. Set `FAILED`; explain honestly;
   state whether rollback occurred or is needed. 3. Sync and verify immediately.
4. Do not commit, push, or deploy failed work unless explicitly directed for diagnostics.

Never include secrets or full sensitive logs in any of these states.
